  "body": "### Description of the Issue\r\n\r\nOn Nov 2nd, MetaMask is going to change their method for injecting an ethereum provider, to require pages to poll for it first. Then MM users will be requested for approval. This will be a breaking change for MM users. \r\n\r\n###### Initial announcement:\r\nhttps://medium.com/metamask/https-medium-com-metamask-breaking-change-injecting-web3-7722797916a8\r\n\r\n> In order to better protect user privacy, MetaMask and other dapp browsers will stop automatically injecting an Ethereum provider or a Web3 instance at page load time. Instead, dapps must request a provider from the browser, which will in turn ask the user to approve or deny access to the Ethereum blockchain. If the user approves access, a provider will be injected into the webpage and the dapp can start up normally.\r\n\r\n###### Current implementation:\r\nCurrent implementation for testing for Web3 is here: https://github.com/MyCryptoHQ/MyCrypto/blob/3074e50909495d171edff2ec63a3e30bbeeb335a/common/libs/nodes/web3/index.ts#L61-L63\r\n\r\nEIP Specification: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1102\r\nEthereum Magicians Thread: https://ethereum-magicians.org/t/eip-1102-opt-in-provider-access/414/46\r\nEIP UX Thread: https://ethereum-magicians.org/t/the-ux-of-eip-1102/814/13\r\n",
